Virtual Patch Panel

dpdk-2.1_rc4 files + patch_panel at /dpdk-2.1_rc4/examples/multi_process
 
Instruction to run the app:-

Building :

First build dpdk by following the dpdk setup guide.

Second set the RTE_SDK environment variable to the dpdk directory.

type make.  This will build patch_panel and nfv.

Usage :

Patch panel
sudo ./patch_panel/patch_panel/x86_64-native-linuxapp-gcc/patch_panel -c 0x02 -n 4 --proc-type=primary -- -p 0x03 -n 2
 
Prompt:-
Add client 0, with phy rx port 0
main > 0; add rx 0(set save position to 1)
main > 0; add tx 0
main > 0; save 1   (set save position to 1)
main > 0; add rx 1
main > 0; add tx 1
main > 0;start
main > 0;loop 0  (set loop thread to handle rx/tx store in position 0)
main > 0;loop 1  (set loop thread to handle rx/tx store in position 1)
 
Start nfv client
sudo ./nfv/nfv/x86_64-native-linuxapp-gcc/app/nfv -c 0x0c -n 4 --pr-type=secondary -- -n 0
 
 
